HEADWORD: Sycoceryl
<hw>Syc`o*ce"ryl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a fig +
<?/ wax + <ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A radical, of
the aromatic series, regarded as an essential ingredient of certain
compounds found in the waxy resin of an Australian species of
fig.</def>⟦br⟧
